The Royal Variety Performance 2015




Award-winning actor and comic Jack Whitehall will host the Royal Variety Performance 2015 at the magnificent Royal Albert Hall in the presence of Prince Harry. Featured performers include Sir Elton John, One Direction, Kylie Minogue, Little Mix, Ricky Martin, Jeff Lynne's ELO, Josh Groban, the Corrs, Brandon Flowers, Beverley Knight and Britain's Got Talent winners Jules, Matisse and Friends. The cast of Mary Poppins perform songs from their show, the spectacular Cirque du Soleil are back in town, and there is also an excerpt from the award-winning comedy The Play That Goes Wrong. Comedy comes from Romesh Ranganathan, Matt Forde and Chris Ramsey.

The show promises to be an unforgettable evening of the best UK and international musical performers, extraordinary theatre, and brilliant comedy as well as a number of sensational surprises.

The event is staged in aid of the Royal Variety Charity (formerly the Entertainment Artistesâ€™ Benevolent Fund), whose patron is Her Majesty The Queen. The money raised from the show helps those people from the world of entertainment in need of care and assistance.
